    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S, a definitive specimen of rotary performance. This vehicle features the 13B-REW power plant with verified factory-spec compression across all rotor faces. The sequential twin-turbocharger assembly operates with surgical precision, providing a seamless transition and holding steady boost pressure through the entire RPM range. The drivetrain is anchored by a crisp 5-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring tactile engagement. The chassis retains its original rigidity, supported by an unmolested double-wishbone suspension setup and a flawless undercarriage. Meticulously maintained with a focus on thermal management and vacuum system integrity, this RX-7 represents a rare opportunity to own a mechanically pure JDM icon in its most pristine state.",
